    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - IDENTIFICATION - GEAR SET IDENTIFICATION (Figure 4 )</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1400903" svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="1">
        <title>GEAR SET IDENTIFICATION (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1400904">Figure 4</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1400904" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1400904" filename="../figg14/G1400904.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 4. Gear Set Identification</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Manufacturer's date</emph>- date gear set was made.
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">401GR128</emph>- part number of ring gear (typical).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Tooth Combination (i.e., 39-11)</emph>- indicates the ring gear has 39 teeth and the
            pinion 11 teeth which results in a 3.54:1 ratio.
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Matched set number</emph>
            - Ring and pinions are manufactured as a matched set. Both pieces are marked with a corresponding number
            (i.e., 268) which identifies them as a matched set.
        </para>
        <para>A gear set that does not have the same matching numbers should not be run together. If either a ring gear
            or pinion requires replacement,
            <emph type="bold">they must be replaced as a matched set.</emph>
        </para>
    </svcproc>
